A 23-year-old man Sunday Freezer, who allegedly poured hot water on his neighbour, was yesterday granted N100,000 bail by an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court. Chief Magistrate J. A. Adegun gave the ruling after the accused pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) Clifford Ogu told the court that the accused committed the offence on June 24 at his residence. Ogu alleged that an argument had ensued between the accused and the complainant, Mr Reuben Afolabi, over the use of the bathroom in the house. “The accused wanted to use the bathroom and the complainant said no and that he got there before him leading to an argument. The accused poured hot water on the complainant’s shoulder,” he said. Adegun adjourned the case till July 10.